Biden Pledged Action to Help His Black Supporters. They Haven’t Forgotten.President-elect Joe Biden told Black voters: “You’ve always had my back, and I’ll have yours.” Many are watching to see what he does, Astead Herndon writes.
Here’s one way President-elect Joe Biden can raise more from the rich without higher taxes.

Behind Trump Clemency, a Case Study in Special AccessPhilip Esformes was sentenced to 20 years for Medicare fraud. Then a well-connected organization supported by his family weighed in with the White House.
A man in Pennsylvania has been accused of illegally voting for President Trump in place of his dead mother.

Analysis: Brexit Is Finally Done, but It Already Seems Out of DateThe idea of an agile “Global Britain” was an effective sales pitch. But that was before President Trump and others began erecting barriers to trade.
Britain and the E.U. struck a landmark trade deal that defines how the two sides will coexist after severing ties.
For the European Union, It’s a Pretty Good DealThe Brexit pact preserves crucial E.U. principles like the single market, and lets the bloc look ahead to its future without Britain.
